Setting up local repository 

1. Create/Initilize a local repository with "git init" command
2. Observe the local repository by "ls -la" (You will be able to see .git folder which is called a local repository)
3. Create some source code. Ex: vi login.java
4. Adding the file to the stage
	$ git add login.java
3. Committing the file to the local repository
	$ git commit login.java -m "login module code"
6. check the log of login.java using the "log" command
	$ git log login.java



1. To get the file/content from git hub.
	$ git clone https://github.com/stvvngrgupta/Devops

2. To check the status of files
	$ git status (Will show the files which are added and commited)

